32 adopt rules addressing, at a minimum, the following: application procedures, capital and liquidity
33 standards, detailed reserve asset requirements, reporting formats, and any other matter that this
34 act assigns to the Commission for specification.
35 SECTION 2.(c) The Commissioner of Banks shall file its first certification under
36 G.S. 53-464(a)(2) within 12 months of the effective date of this section.
37 SECTION 2.(d) A foreign entity, as defined by G.S. 53-462, that, on the effective
38 date of this section, issues a payment stablecoin accessible by residents of this State and that does
